data.text:
James Stroud is a contestant from ​Survivor: Pulau Tiga.

Profile[]

Retrieved from itv-survivor.co.uk

Name: James

Age: 40

From: London

Marital Status: Married

Occupation: Property Developer

Luxury Item: Mirror (for contact lenses)

The Old Etonian property developer was born and brought up in Surrey and now lives in Wimbledon with his wife Caroline and their five children. He's got a BA in Geography and his favourite shop is traveller's paradise Stanfords.

He's passionate about expeditions and exploration, fitting in an adventure trip every three years. His latest adventure was a six-week trek through Nepal and he's roughed it everywhere from Latin America to the Himalayas.

Fairness is important to James, but he's prepared to make exceptions for a game with such high stakes. He enjoys privacy and reading - his favourites include Candide and Tintin - but doesn't get many opportunities to be on his own.[2]

Post-Survivor[]

On 18 August 2001, James, alongside Zoe Lyons, appeared on a reality TV special edition of The Weakest Link. The other contestants on the show appeared on either Castaway 2000, Big Brother 1 or Big Brother 2. He was voted out in Round 7, one round short of the final.
